    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df = df.drop(columns=[\"id\", \"Unnamed: 32\"], errors='ignore')\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "df[\"diagnosis\"] = df[\"diagnosis\"].map({\n",
        "    \"M\": 1,   # Malignant\n",
        "    \"B\": 0    # Benign\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "X = df.drop(columns=[\"diagnosis\"])\n",
        "y = df[\"diagnosis\"]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rgEXgalW2nNF"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "w3Wyz5KS2oFE"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X_scaled, y,\n",
        "    test_size=0.2,\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7rFHd9PP2zIM"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "class_weights = compute_class_weight(\n",
        "    class_weight='balanced',\n",
        "    classes=np.unique(y_train),\n",
        "    y=y_train\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "class_weights = dict(enumerate(class_weights))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nClass Weights:\", class_weights)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "tb4BiEhCKp3L",
        "outputId": "04046339-46c0-46ef-8d66-062e56e886ce"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "\n",
            "Class Weights: {0: np.float64(0.7954545454545454), 1: np.float64(1.3461538461538463)}\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu',\n",
        "                 kernel_initializer='he_normal',\n",
        "                 input_shape=(X.shape[1],)),\n",
        "    layers.Dropout(0.3),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(32, activation='relu',\n",
        "                 kernel_initializer='he_normal'),\n",
        "    layers.Dropout(0.3),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(16, activation='relu',\n",
        "                 kernel_initializer='he_normal'),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(\n",
        "    optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.0005),\n",
        "    loss='binary_crossentropy',\n",
        "    metrics=['accuracy']\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WYipsWa421rE"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "early_stop = EarlyStopping(\n",
        "    monitor='val_loss',\n",
        "    patience=5,\n",
        "    restore_best_weights=True\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "h5DMySkh23ys"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "history = model.fit(\n",
        "    X_train, y_train,\n",
        "    validation_split=0.2,\n",
        "    epochs=100,\n",
        "    batch_size=32,\n",
        "    callbacks=[early_stop],\n",
        "    class_weight=class_weights\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
